Reasoning: The paper uses a dynamic topic modeling approach based on Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF) to analyze the content of legislative speeches in the European Parliament. This involves natural language processing techniques and machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the methodology and technical aspects of the NMF approach, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of signal processing (cs.SI) and data science (cs.DS).
